  "decision_conditions": [
    "REASON: The proposed rear infill extension and 2.5-strorey replacement closet wing and associated alterations to the rear elevation, by virtue of the unsympathetic scale and design, would adversely affect the visual amenity of the Barnsbury Conservation Area and the special architectural and historic interest of the listed building. The works would therefore cause less than substantial to the significance of the heritage assets without public benefits to outweigh this harm. The proposal is therefore contrary to the NPPF 2021, policies D4 and HC1 of the London Plan 2021, policies CS8 and CS9 of the Core Strategy 2011, policies DM2.1 and DM2.3 of the Development Management Policies 2013, the guidance contained within the Urban Design Guide 2017 and the Conservation Area Design Guidelines 2002."
